On the anniversary of the birth of Guru Nanak Dev Ji, the first Sikh Guru, President Obama sends his best wishes to all those observing. He highlights the fundamental principles of Sikhism, such as equality, living an honest life, and serving others. He mentions that the White House hosted the first celebration of Guru Nanak's birth during his presidency and expresses gratitude for the contributions of Sikh Americans to the nation. The President encourages everyone to draw inspiration from Guru Nanak's message of equality, honesty, and helping those in need.